quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  15,1,"Alif Lām Ra. Those are the signs{1}of the Scripture and an evident Recital{2}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is <i>ayat</i> (singular <i>ayah</i>). <i>Ayah</i> means ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an, like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose. Each such unit is considered a ‘sign’ from God.,footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is <i>Qur’an </i>which literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  15,2,"Perhaps those who have denied will wish they had been Muslims."
  15,3,"Letsg them eat and enjoy and be distracted by(false) hope, for they willcome to know."
  15,4,"For in no way did We annihilate any town except that it had a known written decree."
  15,5,"No community can advance its time, nor can they delay it."
  15,6,"And they said, “O you upon whom the Reminder has been bestowed from on high, very truly you are insane."
  15,7,"If only you would bring us the angels, if you are one of the truthful!”"
  15,8,"<span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “The angels are not bestowed from on high except with the truth,”</span>,footnotes:2:According to Ibn Ashour and other exegetes, ‘with the truth’ means ‘for a purpose’.,footnotes:3:The deniers.
  15,9,"Indeed, We—We alone—have bestowed the Reminder from on high, and We will most surely preserve it."
  15,10,"And most surely We sent(messengers) before yousg to the sects of the ancients,"